rComments: Great Prof! Very interpersonal and cares about getting to know his students and making learning fun.

Professor Kulkarni is my favourite Telfer professor. He conveys the information clearly and rewards students who attend lectures and take an active role in their learning. The assignments and exams are fair. He is also kind, caring, and personable. Professor Sagar is a great resource; his students are fortunate to have him!
The Worst professor in Telfer, didnt even provide final grade for students. The final is difficult and consists of am many long answer questions that we didnt learn from the class.
Terrible professor, does not give our clear grading criteria and has extremely boring lectures where he barely even teaches. Just awful. Avoid.

worst prof ever, isn't clear with his marking criteria, doesn't give you half of your grades so you end up going into the final exam not even knowing what grade you have in the class. super unorganized professor, boring lectures, one of the worst professors in Telfer. avoid if you can.

Wasn't a great prof if you're considering online courses. He can be short with his students, doesn't provide useful feedback or helpful responses to emails, his midterms are more like a race to see how fast you can run out of time. Despite online, he let us know he'd fail us if we didn't attend enough lectures (and they weren't helpful ones either)

Tough grader, but really likes to talk with students as if we're equals. Classes are mostly reading slides (can be tedious), but he breaks it apart with class discussions and Q&A. Final exam and midterm involve a lot of reading and memorizing, and it takes forever to get papers backs.
